        t: "My responsibility was to ensure a perfect migration. I wasn't just a coordinator; I was the 'owner' of the end-to-end process, covering governance, compliance, and crucially, retention of the most valuable clients (HNWI). Failure was not an option - I needed to act as the last line of defense to protect assets, bank reputation, and viability of the entire M&A business.",
        a: "There was intense executive pressure to accelerate the migration in 3 months (vs. 18 months planned) to capture synergies faster. I positioned myself firmly against this pressure. I presented a quantitative risk cost model that calculated: estimated BACEN fine of R$ 50-150M for internal control failures, post-go-live remediation cost of R$ 80-120M, and risk of losing 20-30% of HNWI clients (revenue impact of US$ 40-60M annually). I compared this with the cost of maintaining the original schedule (R$ 25M in additional costs) and showed 4:1 ROI in favor of doing it right the first time. Client retention wasn't my formal scope. However, I realized the commercial team was overloaded managing 1,200+ HNWI clients individually. On my own initiative, I assumed ownership of this critical gap: I designed and led a proactive communication campaign segmented by client profile (Ultra-High, High, and Affluent), creating 3 different communication streams with personalized messaging. Standard consultancy reports were weekly and aggregated, masking emerging risks. I identified this blind spot and created my own solution: I built dashboards in Tableau and VBA that crossed data from 7 different systems (core banking, CRM, compliance, risk, accounting) and were updated daily. This allowed me to detect compliance anomalies, validation gaps, and client concerns in real time, not just after they became problems. To manage global teams (12 people in India, 8 in Poland, 6 in China), I instituted a daily 30-minute meeting (6:30am São Paulo, overlap with all time zones). More importantly: I created a unique 'Data Validation Framework' with 47 specific rules and objective KPIs, which served as our universal technical language, overcoming cultural barriers and ensuring zero ambiguity in execution.",
        r: "We migrated 2.7 million accounts and US$ 3.2 billion in assets with zero data loss - a result that placed this migration in the top 5% of global banking M&A migrations, according to HSBC Global PMO benchmarks. We achieved 100% compliance with FATCA and BACEN, passing all audits without a single exception (vs. industry average of 3-5 exceptions per migration of this magnitude). The Private Banking portfolio grew from US$ 480M to US$ 624M (30%, +US$ 144M) during the 18-month transition - proof that proactive communication maintained HNWI confidence while competitors lost clients during their own migrations. As a result, I received formal recognition from the Banquo program director and was cited in C-Level closing reports as one of 3 key leaders responsible for program success for my exceptional ownership.",
