          q_en: "The technical solution involved multiple systems. Did you face integration challenges or resistance from technical teams? How did you solve them?",
          a_en: "Yes, major challenge was that each system had different data formats and business logic. For example, SAP stored dates in DD/MM/YYYY format while Swift used YYYYMMDD. I overcame this by: 1) Creating data mapping tables to standardize formats, 2) Working directly with DBAs to understand schema structures, and 3) Building comprehensive test scripts that validated each conversion. Resistance was minimal because I demonstrated clear business case and provided technical solutions, not just requirements."
